The '''Thrawn Pincer''' was a [[Realspace/Legends|space]] warfare tactic developed by [[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Gial Ackbar/Legends|Gial Ackbar]] shortly after [[Grand Admiral/Legends|Grand Admiral]] [[Mitth'raw'nuruodo/Legends|Thrawn's]] [[Thrawn campaign|war]] on the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]]. It was based on the [[Immobilizer 418 Interdictor-class Heavy Cruiser|Interdictor]] tactics brilliantly employed by the Grand Admiral to bring reinforcements into his [[Siege of Coruscant|attack]] on [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] and in other battles.

==Characteristics==
[[File:ThrawnInterdictor.jpg|thumb|left|250px|Grand Admiral Thrawn]]
It started with a main task force being divided into two. The first group would drop into an enemy [[Star system/Legends|system]] and engage the enemy fleet while the second would jump into a nearby system. When the enemy fleet activated its [[Gravity well projector/Legends|gravity well projectors]], the [[Commander/Legends|commander]] would then order the second fleet to make a [[Precision hyperspace jump|micro-jump]] through [[Hyperspace/Legends|hyperspace]], usually behind the enemy fleet. Ordinarily, a ship would come out of hyperspace without precise control of where it stopped, requiring it to continue traveling at sublight speeds to reach its intended destination. The advantage of this tactic, then, was that it permitted a fleet to come out of hyperspace at a precise, knowable position.<ref name="IR" />

==History==
This tactic was notably used during the [[Battle of Ciutric]] that occurred in [[9 ABY]] against [[Prince/Legends|Prince]]-[[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Delak Krennel]]. It resulted in his [[Death/Legends|death]] and the victory of New Republic forces.<ref name="IR" />

Another form of this tactic was used during the [[Second Battle of Bilbringi]], but it involved three fleets; one [[Imperial Remnant|Imperial]], led by [[Grand Admiral/Legends|Grand Admiral]] [[Gilad Pellaeon/Legends|Gilad Pellaeon]], and two of New Republic, led by Admiral [[Sien Sovv]] and [[General/Legends|General]] [[Wedge Antilles/Legends|Wedge Antilles]].<ref name="IR" />

